            <h2>Common SAML assertion errors</h2>
            <p>Understanding common SAML errors helps diagnose authentication failures quickly.</p>

            <h3>Invalid Signature</h3>
            <p>A signature validation failure indicates the assertion was modified after signing, or the wrong certificate was used. Verify you have the current IdP certificate and that the SP is configured to trust it. Certificate rotation without SP updates is a common cause.</p>

            <h3>Audience Mismatch</h3>
            <p>The assertion's Audience element must match the SP's Entity ID exactly. A mismatch indicates the assertion was intended for a different SP or the SP configuration is incorrect.</p>

            <h3>Timestamp Validation Failures</h3>
            <p>Conditions/NotOnOrAfter errors indicate the assertion has expired. Check server clocks for synchronization. Assertions with future NotBefore times indicate clock skew between IdP and SP.</p>

            <h2>Common OIDC token errors</h2>
            <h3>Invalid Issuer</h3>
            <p>The token's iss claim must exactly match the expected issuer URL. Query parameters, trailing slashes, and case sensitivity all matter. Verify the issuer configuration matches the OIDC discovery document.</p>

            <h3>Invalid Audience</h3>
            <p>The token's aud claim must include the client's registered identifier. For single-audience tokens, aud is a string. For multiple audiences, aud is an array.</p>

            <h3>Token Expired</h3>
            <p>The exp claim indicates expiration. ID tokens typically have short lifetimes (15-60 minutes). If exp is in the past, the token has expired and a new one must be obtained.</p>

            <h2>Signature verification in browser environments</h2>
            <p>Browser-based signature verification for OIDC tokens signed with RS256 or ES256 requires access to the IdP's JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint. This tool performs basic decoding and validation but cannot verify asymmetric signatures without the public key.</p>
            <p>For production SSO testing, use dedicated libraries that properly implement signature verification, key caching, and algorithm validation according to OIDC specifications.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. FAQ Component -->
    <section class="component-section">
        <span class="component-label">Component 7 / FAQ</span>
        <div class="faq-grid">
            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>How do I troubleshoot a SAML 'Invalid Signature' error?</h3>
                <p>Verify you have the correct IdP certificate configured in your SP. Check that the certificate hasn't expired or been rotated. Ensure the XML was not modified after signing. Use this tool to validate the signature with the current certificate.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>What information is extracted from a SAML assertion?</h3>
                <p>Common extractions include: NameID (user identifier), attributes (email, name, groups), Issuer, Conditions (timestamps, audience), and signature status. The tool displays all parseable elements in a structured format.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>Why is my OIDC ID token failing validation in this tool?</h3>
                <p>Common causes: expired token (exp in the past), issuer mismatch, audience mismatch, or malformed JWT structure. Check that the issuer and audience values match your OIDC provider configuration exactly.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is my SSO data stored or logged during the testing process?</h3>
                <p>No. All processing happens entirely in your browser. No SAML responses, OIDC tokens, certificates, or validation results are transmitted or stored externally.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>How do I check if my SAML response contains the correct attributes for my application?</h3>
                <p>Paste the SAML response in the tool and examine the Decoded Attributes section. Verify that required attributes like email, name, and groups are present and contain expected values. Compare against your SP's expected attribute mapping configuration.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-item">
                <h3>Can I test OIDC tokens signed with RS256 in this tool?</h3>
                <p>This tool can decode and validate the claims structure, but browser-based RS256 signature verification requires the IdP's public key or JWKS endpoint. Use the tool to inspect claims while implementing proper signature verification in your application backend.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Internal Discovery Component -->
    <section class="component-section">
        <span class="component-label">Component 8 / Internal Discovery</span>
        <div class="discovery-grid">
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools/jwt-decoder">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔓</div>
                <h3>JWT Decoder</h3>
                <p>Decode and inspect JWT tokens to verify payloads, headers, and signature status.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools/jwt-generator">
                <div class="discovery-icon">✍️</div>
                <h3>JWT Generator</h3>
                <p>Create and sign custom JSON Web Tokens for API authentication testing.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools/oauth-flow-visualizer">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔄</div>
                <h3>OAuth 2.0 Visualizer</h3>
                <p>Visualize OAuth 2.0 authentication flows with sequence diagrams and security recommendations.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔐</div>
                <h3>X.509 Certificate Parser</h3>
                <p>Parse and inspect X.509 certificates to view subject, issuer, and validity dates.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools/api-key-generator">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔑</div>
                <h3>API Key Generator</h3>
                <p>Generate secure API tokens with custom permissions and TTL for granular access control.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools/session-token-analyzer">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔍</div>
                <h3>Session Token Analyzer</h3>
                <p>Analyze session tokens and JWTs for security properties and vulnerability detection.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🌐</div>
                <h3>SAML Metadata Generator</h3>
                <p>Generate SAML 2.0 SP metadata XML for Service Provider configuration.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="discovery-card" href="/tools">
                <div class="discovery-icon">🔒</div>
                <h3>Password Generator</h3>
                <p>Create strong, random passwords with customizable character sets and length.</p>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>

<script>
(function() {
    const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
    const show = (el) => el.style.display = 'block';
    const hide = (el) => el.style.display = 'none';

    const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tool-tab');
    const samlTab = $('samlTab');
    const oidcTab = $('oidcTab');

    const samlInput = $('samlInput');
    const idpCert = $('idpCert');
    const oidcInput = $('oidcInput');
    const oidcIssuer = $('oidcIssuer');
    const oidcAudience = $('oidcAudience');
    const spEntityId = $('spEntityId');
    const validateBtn = $('validateBtn');
    const clearBtn = $('clearBtn');

    const placeholderMessage = $('placeholderMessage');
    const errorDisplay = $('errorDisplay');
    const resultsDisplay = $('resultsDisplay');
    const validationResults = $('validationResults');
    const decodedClaims = $('decodedClaims');
    const timestampResults = $('timestampResults');
    const troubleshootSection = $('troubleshootSection');
    const troubleshootList = $('troubleshootList');

    let currentTab = 'saml';

    tabs.forEach(tab => {
        tab.addEventListener('click', function() {
            tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
            this.classList.add('active');
            currentTab = this.dataset.tab;
            samlTab.classList.toggle('active', currentTab === 'saml');
            oidcTab.classList.toggle('active', currentTab === 'oidc');
        });
    });

    function escapeHtml(text) {
        const div = document.createElement('div');
        div.textContent = text;
        return div.innerHTML;
    }

    function syntaxHighlightJSON(json) {
        if (typeof json === 'string') {
            try { json = JSON.parse(json); } catch (e) { return escapeHtml(json); }
        }
        const str = JSON.stringify(json, null, 2);
        return str.replace(/("(\\u[a-zA-Z0-9]{4}|\\[^u]|[^\\"])*"(\s*:)?|\b(true|false|null)\b|-?\d+(?:\.\d*)?(?:[eE][+\-]?\d+)?)/g, function (match) {
            let cls = 'json-number';
            if (/^"/.test(match)) {
                if (/:$/.test(match)) {
                    cls = 'json-key';
                    match = match.slice(0, -1);
                    return '<span class="' + cls + '">' + escapeHtml(match) + '</span>:';
                } else { cls = 'json-string'; }
            } else if (/true|false/.test(match)) { cls = 'json-number'; }
            return '<span class="' + cls + '">' + escapeHtml(match) + '</span>';
        });
    }

    function base64Decode(str) {
        str = str.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');
        while (str.length % 4) str += '=';
        try {
            return atob(str);
        } catch (e) {
            return null;
        }
    }

    function showError(message) {
        hide(placeholderMessage);
        hide(resultsDisplay);
        errorDisplay.textContent = message;
        show(errorDisplay);
    }

    function addValidationCard(type, title, description) {
        const card = document.createElement('div');
        card.className = 'validation-card ' + type;
        card.innerHTML = '<div class="validation-title">' + title + '</div><div class="validation-description">' + description + '</div>';
        validationResults.appendChild(card);
    }

    function formatTimestamp(unix) {
        if (!unix) return '-';
        return new Date(unix * 1000).toLocaleString();
    }

    function validateSAML() {
        const input = samlInput.value.trim();
        if (!input) {
            showError('Please enter a SAML response.');
            return;
        }

        let xmlString = input;
        if (!input.includes('<') && input.includes('==')) {
            const decoded = base64Decode(input);
            if (decoded) xmlString = decoded;
        }

        try {
            const parser = new DOMParser();
            const xmlDoc = parser.parseFromString(xmlString, 'text/xml');

            const parseError = xmlDoc.querySelector('parsererror');
            if (parseError) {
                showError('Invalid XML format. Please check that you have pasted a valid SAML response.');
                return;
            }

            const ns = {
                saml: 'urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:assertion',
                samlp: 'urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:protocol'
            };

            const assertion = xmlDoc.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Assertion')[0] || xmlDoc.querySelector('Assertion');
            if (!assertion) {
                showError('No SAML Assertion found in the response.');
                return;
            }

            const expectedAudience = spEntityId.value.trim();

            const results = {
                issuer: '',
                nameId: '',
                attributes: {},
                conditions: {},
                signatureStatus: 'unsigned'
            };

            const issuerEl = assertion.querySelector('Issuer') || assertion.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Issuer')[0];
            if (issuerEl) results.issuer = issuerEl.textContent;

            const nameIdEl = assertion.querySelector('NameID') || assertion.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'NameID')[0];
            if (nameIdEl) results.nameId = nameIdEl.textContent;

            const subjectEl = assertion.querySelector('Subject') || assertion.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Subject')[0];
            if (subjectEl && !nameIdEl) {
                const nid = subjectEl.querySelector('NameID') || subjectEl.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'NameID')[0];
                if (nid) results.nameId = nid.textContent;
            }

            const attributeStatement = assertion.querySelector('AttributeStatement') || assertion.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'AttributeStatement')[0];
            if (attributeStatement) {
                const attrs = attributeStatement.querySelectorAll('Attribute') || attributeStatement.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Attribute');
                for (let i = 0; i < attrs.length; i++) {
                    const name = attrs[i].getAttribute('Name') || attrs[i].getAttribute('FriendlyName');
                    let value = '';
                    const attrValue = attrs[i].querySelector('AttributeValue') || attrs[i].getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'AttributeValue')[0];
                    if (attrValue) value = attrValue.textContent;
                    if (name) results.attributes[name] = value;
                }
            }

            const conditions = assertion.querySelector('Conditions') || assertion.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Conditions')[0];
            if (conditions) {
                results.conditions.notBefore = conditions.getAttribute('NotBefore');
                results.conditions.notOnOrAfter = conditions.getAttribute('NotOnOrAfter');
                const audienceEl = conditions.querySelector('Audience') || conditions.getElementsByTagNameNS(ns.saml, 'Audience')[0];
                if (audienceEl) results.conditions.audience = audienceEl.textContent;
            }

            const signature = assertion.querySelector('Signature') || xmlDoc.querySelector('Signature');
            if (signature) results.signatureStatus = 'present';

            hide(placeholderMessage);
            hide(errorDisplay);
            show(resultsDisplay);
            validationResults.innerHTML = '';
            troubleshootSection.style.display = 'none';
            troubleshootList.innerHTML = '';

            if (results.issuer) {
                addValidationCard('info', 'Issuer: ' + escapeHtml(results.issuer), 'The Identity Provider that issued this assertion.');
            }

            if (results.signatureStatus === 'present') {
                if (idpCert.value.trim()) {
                    addValidationCard('warning', 'Signature Present', 'Cryptographic signature verification requires server-side processing with the IdP certificate. Browser-based XML signature validation is limited.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('warning', 'Signature Present (No Certificate)', 'Provide the IdP certificate above to verify the signature.');
                }
            } else {
                addValidationCard('error', 'No Signature', 'This assertion is not digitally signed. Unsigned assertions are vulnerable to tampering.');
            }

            const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
            const issues = [];

            if (results.conditions.notBefore) {
                const notBefore = Math.floor(new Date(results.conditions.notBefore).getTime() / 1000);
                if (notBefore > now) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'NotBefore Error', 'The assertion is not yet valid. This indicates clock skew between the IdP and current time.');
                    issues.push('<strong>NotBefore in future:</strong> Check clock synchronization between IdP and SP.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'NotBefore Valid', 'Assertion is within valid time window.');
                }
            }

            if (results.conditions.notOnOrAfter) {
                const notOnOrAfter = Math.floor(new Date(results.conditions.notOnOrAfter).getTime() / 1000);
                if (notOnOrAfter < now) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Assertion Expired', 'The assertion has expired (NotOnOrAfter: ' + formatTimestamp(notOnOrAfter) + ').');
                    issues.push('<strong>Assertion expired:</strong> Request a new assertion from the IdP or check session timeout settings.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'Expiration Valid', 'Assertion expires at: ' + formatTimestamp(notOnOrAfter));
                }
            }

            if (expectedAudience && results.conditions.audience) {
                if (results.conditions.audience === expectedAudience) {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'Audience Match', 'Audience (' + escapeHtml(results.conditions.audience) + ') matches expected Entity ID.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Audience Mismatch', 'Expected: ' + escapeHtml(expectedAudience) + ', Found: ' + escapeHtml(results.conditions.audience));
                    issues.push('<strong>Audience mismatch:</strong> Configure the SP Entity ID to match: ' + escapeHtml(results.conditions.audience));
                }
            }

            decodedClaims.innerHTML = syntaxHighlightJSON({
                issuer: results.issuer || 'Not specified',
                nameId: results.nameId || 'Not specified',
                audience: results.conditions.audience || 'Not specified',
                notBefore: results.conditions.notBefore || 'Not specified',
                notOnOrAfter: results.conditions.notOnOrAfter || 'Not specified',
                attributes: Object.keys(results.attributes).length > 0 ? results.attributes : 'No attributes found'
            });

            timestampResults.innerHTML = '';

            if (issues.length > 0) {
                troubleshootSection.style.display = 'block';
                issues.forEach(issue => {
                    const item = document.createElement('div');
                    item.className = 'troubleshoot-item';
                    item.innerHTML = issue;
                    troubleshootList.appendChild(item);
                });
            }

        } catch (error) {
            showError('Failed to parse SAML response: ' + error.message);
        }
    }

    function validateOIDC() {
        const token = oidcInput.value.trim();
        if (!token) {
            showError('Please enter an OIDC ID token.');
            return;
        }

        const parts = token.split('.');
        if (parts.length !== 3) {
            showError('Invalid JWT format. An ID token must have three segments separated by dots.');
            return;
        }

        try {
            const headerJson = base64Decode(parts[0]);
            const payloadJson = base64Decode(parts[1]);

            if (!headerJson || !payloadJson) {
                showError('Failed to decode JWT segments. The token may be malformed.');
                return;
            }

            let header, payload;
            try {
                header = JSON.parse(headerJson);
            } catch (e) {
                showError('Failed to parse token header as JSON.');
                return;
            }

            try {
                payload = JSON.parse(payloadJson);
            } catch (e) {
                showError('Failed to parse token payload as JSON.');
                return;
            }

            hide(placeholderMessage);
            hide(errorDisplay);
            show(resultsDisplay);
            validationResults.innerHTML = '';
            troubleshootSection.style.display = 'none';
            troubleshootList.innerHTML = '';

            const expectedIssuer = oidcIssuer.value.trim();
            const expectedAudience = oidcAudience.value.trim();
            const issues = [];

            if (payload.iss) {
                if (expectedIssuer && payload.iss === expectedIssuer) {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'Issuer Valid', 'Token issuer matches expected value.');
                } else if (expectedIssuer) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Issuer Mismatch', 'Expected: ' + escapeHtml(expectedIssuer) + ', Found: ' + escapeHtml(payload.iss));
                    issues.push('<strong>Issuer mismatch:</strong> Verify your OIDC provider configuration and expected issuer URL.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('info', 'Issuer: ' + escapeHtml(payload.iss), 'No expected issuer configured for comparison.');
                }
            }

            if (payload.aud) {
                const audArray = Array.isArray(payload.aud) ? payload.aud : [payload.aud];
                if (expectedAudience && audArray.includes(expectedAudience)) {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'Audience Valid', 'Token audience matches expected client ID.');
                } else if (expectedAudience && !audArray.includes(expectedAudience)) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Audience Mismatch', 'Expected: ' + escapeHtml(expectedAudience) + ', Found: ' + audArray.join(', '));
                    issues.push('<strong>Audience mismatch:</strong> Ensure your application\'s client ID is registered with the OIDC provider.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('info', 'Audience: ' + audArray.join(', '), 'No expected audience configured for comparison.');
                }
            }

            const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);

            if (payload.iat) {
                const iat = parseInt(payload.iat, 10);
                addValidationCard('info', 'Issued At: ' + formatTimestamp(iat), 'Token creation timestamp.');
            }

            if (payload.exp) {
                const exp = parseInt(payload.exp, 10);
                if (exp < now) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Token Expired', 'Token expired at: ' + formatTimestamp(exp));
                    issues.push('<strong>Token expired:</strong> Obtain a new ID token from the OIDC provider.');
                } else {
                    addValidationCard('success', 'Expiration Valid', 'Token expires at: ' + formatTimestamp(exp));
                }
            }

            if (payload.nbf) {
                const nbf = parseInt(payload.nbf, 10);
                if (nbf > now) {
                    addValidationCard('error', 'Token Not Yet Valid', 'Token becomes valid at: ' + formatTimestamp(nbf));
                    issues.push('<strong>Token not yet valid:</strong> Check clock synchronization or wait until the nbf time.');
                }
            }

            const claimsDisplay = {
                iss: payload.iss || 'Not specified',
                sub: payload.sub || 'Not specified',
                aud: payload.aud || 'Not specified',
                exp: payload.exp ? formatTimestamp(payload.exp) : 'Not specified',
                iat: payload.iat ? formatTimestamp(payload.iat) : 'Not specified',
                nbf: payload.nbf ? formatTimestamp(payload.nbf) : 'Not specified',
                nonce: payload.nonce || 'Not specified',
                email: payload.email || 'Not specified',
                name: payload.name || 'Not specified',
                amr: payload.amr ? payload.amr.join(', ') : 'Not specified'
            };

            decodedClaims.innerHTML = syntaxHighlightJSON(claimsDisplay);

            if (issues.length > 0) {
                troubleshootSection.style.display = 'block';
                issues.forEach(issue => {
                    const item = document.createElement('div');
                    item.className = 'troubleshoot-item';
                    item.innerHTML = issue;
                    troubleshootList.appendChild(item);
                });
            }

        } catch (error) {
            showError('Failed to parse ID token: ' + error.message);
        }
    }

    function validate() {
        if (currentTab === 'saml') {
            validateSAML();
        } else {
            validateOIDC();
        }
    }

    function clearAll() {
        hide(errorDisplay);
        hide(resultsDisplay);
        show(placeholderMessage);
        validationResults.innerHTML = '';
        samlInput.value = '';
        idpCert.value = '';
        oidcInput.value = '';
        oidcIssuer.value = '';
        oidcAudience.value = '';
        spEntityId.value = '';
        troubleshootSection.style.display = 'none';
        troubleshootList.innerHTML = '';
    }

    validateBtn.addEventListener('click', validate);
    clearBtn.addEventListener('click', clearAll);
})();
</script>

<!-- 1. Global Layout Components: Footer -->
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
